# .cursorrules — paste this into every Next.js project

Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Supabase

Code Style:

- Use TypeScript always. Define proper types and interfaces.
- Prefer Server Components. Add 'use client' only when required (event handlers, hooks).
- Use Server Actions for mutations (forms, data writes) in /actions/ folder.
- Use Supabase server client (createServerClient) in server components.
- Use Supabase browser client (createBrowserClient) in client components.

Structure:

- Components go in /components/features/ (your components) or /components/ui/ (shadcn).
- Shared types go in /lib/types.ts.
- Utility functions go in /lib/utils.ts.
- All Supabase queries go in /lib/queries.ts for reuse.

Responses:

- Always explain what you changed and why.
- Flag potential security issues (missing auth checks, exposed secrets).
- Suggest error handling if I haven't included it.
- Keep components small (under 150 lines). Suggest splitting if larger.
